nd support for Palestinian nationalism. It is a perspective which has gradually gained ground in the political mainstream.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aArab-Israeli conflict. 0aLabor ZionismxHistory. 0aLabor Zionism-History. 0aZionism. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aBritish left.  aIsrael/Palestinian conflict.  aLabour Party.  aPalestine.  aZionist movement.1 aKelemen, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130358423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130358/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013